<font color="#FF0000">COMMENTS TO POV</font><br>
<tt>Fri Apr  4 19:48:18 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Nothing in its life became it like the leaving of it!<br><br>
The imminent demise of this web site appears to have engendered the same variety of opinions and the same vitriol that the site itself engendered during its life.  It has all been said - perhaps ad nauseam - and the events of 20-35 years ago have lost most of the immediacy they once had.  Those who have moved on have moved very far.  Others have not moved on and, for whatever reasons, seem somehow stuck in time.  The site has served its purpose - perhaps too well - and empowered the agonizing; the cartharsis; the raging against the circumstances, people and events; the introspection; the regrets; whatever the individual felt.  Like the war and the experience, it is time to put the site behind us.  <br><br>
IT'S OVER, OUT.<br><br>
CSMO
